#: ./security-guide/section_hardening-the-virtualization-layers.xml:239(para)
msgid "Compiler hardening makes it more difficult to attack the QEMU process. However, if an attacker does succeed, we would like to limit the impact of the attack. Mandatory access controls accomplish this by restricting the privileges on QEMU process to only what is needed. This can be accomplished using sVirt / SELinux or AppArmor. When using sVirt, SELinux is configured to run every QEMU process under a different security context. AppArmor can be configured to provide similar functionality. We provide more details on sVirt in the instance isolation section below."
