msgid "Security considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ./security-guide/section_continuous-systems-management.xml:254(para)
msgid "Ensure only authenticated users and backup clients have access to the backup server."
msgstr ""

#: ./security-guide/section_continuous-systems-management.xml:258(para)
msgid "Use data encryption options for storage and transmission of backups."
msgstr ""

#: ./security-guide/section_continuous-systems-management.xml:262(para)
msgid "Use a dedicated and hardened backup servers. The logs for the backup server must be monitored daily and accessible by only few individuals."
msgstr ""

#: ./security-guide/section_continuous-systems-management.xml:267(para)
msgid "Test data recovery options regularly. One of the things that can be restored from secured backups is the images. In case of a compromise, the best practice would be to terminate running instances immediately and then relaunch the instances from the images in the secured backup repository."
